# Shadpine UI

**Shadpine UI** is this project’s **Alpine.js** component kit **inspired by [shadcn/ui](https://ui.shadcn.com/)** (API, structure, and visuals). It is **conceptually framework-agnostic**: you need **Alpine**, a **templating layer** (this repo uses **Blade** / PHP; you could adapt markup to **Astro**, etc.), and a **styling approach** — **Tailwind** by default (with PHP **Tailwind Merge** as `$tw` here), but the same patterns can use **plain CSS classes** if you replace utilities.

**This template’s implementation** lives under **`web/app/themes/{THEME_SLUG}/`** (`sage` until renamed). **Goal:** mirror named shadcn/ui widgets **1:1** in behavior and override story where practical, without React/Radix.

## Project default

- **Prefer Shadpine UI** (`resources/views/components/`) for interactive and styled UI instead of ad-hoc markup in templates, flexible layouts, and blocks—unless a third-party pattern is explicitly required.

## Layering (shadcn-style split)

| Layer | Responsibility | Location (this repo) |
|-------|----------------|----------------------|
| **Primitive** | **Radix-parity behavior:** roles, ARIA, keyboard/focus, and **all Alpine** for this widget (`x-data` on root, `x-teleport`, `x-trap`, `x-show`, `x-on:*`, `x-bind` for `aria-*`, etc.). **No** heavy Tailwind here—only pass through `class` from the styled parent via `$attributes` when needed. Props / logic → **`App\View\Components\{Name}\Primitive\*.php`**; **`primitive/*.blade.php`** stays **markup-only** (no **`@props`** / **`@php`**). | `resources/views/components/{name}/primitive/*.blade.php` + `app/View/Components/{Name}/Primitive/` |
| **Styled** | Default Tailwind only (merged in **`App\View\Components/{Name}/*.php`** **`render()`**), slots, **`data-slot`**; composes **`<x-{name}.primitive.*>`** — Blade file is **markup-only** (no **`@props`** / **`@php`**) | `resources/views/components/{name}/*.blade.php` (outside `primitive/`) |
| **Alpine logic** | Typed `Alpine.data(...)` factories; no heavy logic in Blade | `resources/ts/components/{name}/` — **`{name}.ts`** (+ **`index.ts`** barrel); multi-file widgets (e.g. **calendar**) keep helpers in the same folder |
| **Shared class tokens** | **Only** when upstream shadcn exports CVA for reuse (e.g. **`buttonVariants`**) | `config/classes/{name}.php` → `config('classes.{name}')` |
| **One-off layout/appearance** | Default `cn(...)` strings from the registry file, colocated in Blade | `resources/views/components/{name}/*.blade.php` — still use **`$tw->merge(..., $attributes->get('class'))`** |

### `config/classes` vs classes in Blade

- **Add `config/classes/{slug}.php`** only when the shadcn/ui source **exports** a CVA map meant for reuse (example: [Button](https://ui.shadcn.com/docs/components/radix/button) exports **`buttonVariants`**; this repo mirrors that as **`config/classes/button.php`** so **`x-button`**, **`alert-dialog` actions**, etc. stay DRY).
- **Do not** add a `config/classes` file for components whose registry TSX only calls **`cn(...)`** inline with **no** exported **`fooVariants`** (example: [Alert Dialog](https://ui.shadcn.com/docs/components/radix/alert-dialog) — keep overlay/content/header strings **in the Blade partials** next to the markup).
- **Parity:** when the user links a shadcn doc URL, compare class strings against the **current** registry implementation (e.g. `apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/ui/{component}.tsx` in [shadcn-ui/ui](https://github.com/shadcn-ui/ui)), not an remembered older build.

- **Accordion reference:** see **`accordion/`** — e.g. **`accordion/primitive/trigger.blade.php`** (ARIA + `@click` / `@keydown` + `x-id`) vs **`accordion/trigger.blade.php`** (tokens + **`x-accordion.primitive.trigger`**). New widgets follow the same split.
- **Tailwind merge:** `TailwindMerge` is shared to views as **`$tw`** from `ThemeServiceProvider` — merge **base → variants → `$attributes->get('class')`** in **`App\View\Components/*`** **`render()`** (or colocated helpers), then pass the resulting class string into Blade.
- **`data-slot` (mandatory pattern):** Never hardcode **`data-slot="…"`** as a fixed string-only attribute on a Shadpine root or sub-part. Declare the default on the **class component** (camelCase: **`dataSlot`**, or **`wrapperDataSlot` / `selectDataSlot`** when one view renders multiple slotted nodes), output **`data-slot="{{ $dataSlot }}"`** in Blade. Consumers override with **`data-slot`**, **`wrapper-data-slot`**, etc. If Tailwind utilities use literals like **`data-[slot=accordion-trigger-icon]`**, keep those class strings in sync with the prop default or document matching overrides (JIT must still see full utilities in source).
- **Registration:** each Alpine component factory is imported and registered in **`resources/ts/app.ts`** (e.g. `Alpine.data('accordion', accordion)`).

## Interactivity & accessibility

- Any **interactive** or **stateful** pattern (accordion, dialog, menu, tabs, …) **must** use a **`primitive/`** subtree for a11y and behavior; styled wrappers compose primitives (same idea as Radix + shadcn in React).
- Target **WCAG 2.2** at the level appropriate to the pattern (keyboard, focus order, roles, labels, `aria-*`, reduced motion where transitions exist). Validate against the [WAI-ARIA APG](https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/) pattern for that widget.
- **Tests:** ship **Vitest** unit tests colocated under **`resources/ts/components/{name}/`** (e.g. **`accordion/accordion.test.ts`**, **`calendar/calendar.test.ts`**) — any path matched by **`vitest.config.js`**. Cover state transitions, edge cases, and keyboard/helper behavior that is pure TS. Complement with manual or browser checks for full a11y when needed.

### Accessibility checklist (each new interactive primitive)

Complete before treating the primitive as done. Record the **APG pattern URL** in **`docs/components/{name}.md`**.

| # | Check |
|---|--------|
| 1 | **Pattern:** APG (or equivalent) pattern chosen; behavior matches it unless documented deviation. |
| 2 | **Keyboard:** All operable parts reachable by Tab (or pattern-specific roving tabindex); documented keys implemented (↑/↓, Home/End, Escape, Enter/Space on native controls, etc.). |
| 3 | **Roles & states:** Correct `role` (if any), `aria-expanded`, `aria-controls`, `aria-selected`, `aria-hidden`, `aria-labelledby` / `aria-label` as the pattern requires. |
| 4 | **Names:** Every control has a visible label or **accessible name** (text, `aria-label`, or labelled-by); decorative icons **`aria-hidden="true"`**. |
| 5 | **Focus:** Focus order logical; **focus visible** (e.g. `focus-visible:ring-*`); no stuck focus inside hidden content. |
| 6 | **Motion:** **`prefers-reduced-motion`** respected for open/close animations/transitions. |
| 7 | **Automation:** **Vitest** for `resources/ts/components/{name}/`; manual keyboard + SR smoke on a real page for this widget. |

**Human documentation:** add or update **`docs/components/{name}.md`** (props, slots, files, APG link) when adding a component — see **`docs/components/INDEX.md`**.

## Alpine plugins

- Use **`@alpinejs/collapse`**, **`@alpinejs/focus`**, and **any other Alpine official or vetted plugin** when it reduces bugs or improves a11y—**new Composer/npm dependencies still require explicit project approval** per **`01-global-protocols.mdc`**.

## Scope boundaries

- **`resources/views/components/`** is **UI markup only** for Shadpine (Alpine bindings + structure). **No** **`@php`**, **no** **`@props`** — PHP for props/merges lives in **`app/View/Components/`** per **`09-blade-laravel-components.mdc`**. No WordPress queries, business rules, or domain logic—those stay in **`App\View\Composers/*`**, features, or support classes (**`05-theme-php-blade-acf.mdc`**).
- Each widget should map to a **named shadcn/ui component** (document the parity target in **`docs/components/{name}.md`** and PR/commit context when adding).

## Commands & gates

- After TS changes: **`npm run lint`**, **`npm run test`**, **`npm run typecheck`** (**`10-testing-mandatory.mdc`**, **`13-mandatory-lint.mdc`**).
- After Blade/config class changes: theme **`composer run lint`** when PHP is touched; **`npm run build`** if markup/classes affect shipped CSS.

